<subSubSection id="1B2FF8161099BF83B029C6A5F9BFB616" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="E335F7E371E628CBCCB3025FAB3AD4F3" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E4F5266B901CBFF00980A548651555F6" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">The species epithet is derived from the collection locality.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EAC58C04CFD3B1F0D860E9F17FBB14E0" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" type="description">
<paragraph id="76FDF6BE44D0B78B2FF4AB9216FC6E31" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="130324761895BC9F673CF6B24D547E36" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis id="84EFAD62C938C2E787B32A08DB43E4EB" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Female.</emphasis>
Body length 3.16 mm; fore wing length 3.30 mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="79C78B3AECBEA4495114FA16D9319A64" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis id="3E7ED033AB8A0200BA0E958A5C6F5CBF" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Head</emphasis>
1.57
<normalizedToken id="45C56A8B6CB7430432B6BBF811ADE53B" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as wide as long; face sparsely setose, frons bare and eyes densely setose; clypeus 2.46
<normalizedToken id="CA5C0301829BCAFE303E790AE5F89AAF" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as wide as long. OOL/OD: 2.7
<normalizedToken id="B7CC45B0653207C29367D945C7E26355" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
; POL/OD: 2.2
<normalizedToken id="28D4C140F49D8123780AEC4298001E3F" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
. Scape 1.82
<normalizedToken id="C8CE18083221C89426FE1E3E6021266F" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as wide as long; pedicel 1.27
<normalizedToken id="51672C9A98BF05D3632204401A48B8FA" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as wide as long; F2 2.6
<normalizedToken id="30A5F3A0340C79D997CFDFD7C7E92E7A" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide; F14 1.7
<normalizedToken id="A974D64B1FDE5D67EBFCF04D6A0F28C0" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide; F15 1.8
<normalizedToken id="1524EFF1297C11D595AABA731D3D3B0C" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide; F2 L/F14 L: 1.6
<normalizedToken id="889B7890E16113E4E968AB8A563F6034" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5804875DF44CDF16041CCFECBE06E3F2" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis id="E49D72E2ADF8FEFAB2525E57C204E70F" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Mesosoma</emphasis>
1.33
<normalizedToken id="04115D558ACE81D28A02DED0FF43C782" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than wide; mesoscutum sparsely setose and shallowly punctate. Fore wing length: 3.30 mm. Fore wing with vein 3-Cu1 entirely nebulous; vein 1-R1 (0.58) shorter than pterostigma length (0.74) and a little longer than distance delimited between end of vein 1-R1 and end of vein SR1 (0.47). Fore wing with areolet triangular and relatively small, its maximum height 0.33
<normalizedToken id="80A35F5BFCB14EE1CCB058BAFEDB1E40" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
vein r length, its maximum width 0.72
<normalizedToken id="A323103DB59F700FDE51BDF084CC8125" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
vein r length. Length of veins M+Cu1: 1-M: 1.03: 0.33; 1Cu1: 2Cu1:m-cu: 0.19: 0.21:0.18. Propodeum rugose, with rugosity along median transverse area, with trace of some transverse carina; median longitudinal carina complete; propodeal areola absent. Metafemur L/W: 3.6
<normalizedToken id="97D4AB3F1AE266C07686678152D2AE2B" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="396C20D8F864217658297766936AD08D" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis id="E2CE2CDC515FADADC7C12118CA178CF6" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Metasoma.</emphasis>
T1 parallel sided and strongly longitudinally striate, T2 longitudinally striate on lateral sides and basal half, remaining tergites smooth and shiny. T1 median length 2
<normalizedToken id="9F0A191418E78F83EDC7B8F219B3E473" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
its width at posterior margin; T2 width at posterior margin 2.29
<normalizedToken id="1EDF638F217B84415BB1C817ED3F1D49" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
its median length. Hind tibia L: 1.14 mm. Ovipositor sheath L: 0.44 mm. Hind tibia length 2.59
<normalizedToken id="A2707DD3D2B1B279FB3BB9DEC42FEE70" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
length of ovipositor sheath. Maximum length of setae on ovipositor sheath (0.09) at most slightly longer than maximum width of ovipositor sheath (0.06). Hypopygium sclerotized.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BCA1E4B2EFB682ECF8D925F586D17E5D" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis id="BD0D34AEBE9549658F9644C5B768374A" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Colour.</emphasis>
Female (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B74756F41C78731776604C6F8A07F1BD" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Paroplitis khajjiarensis Gupta &amp; Fernandez-Triana sp. nov. A male in habitus (lateral view) B female fore wing C female (in dorsal aspect) D female F 10 - F 15 E female F 1 - F 3 F female head in frontal view G female vertex H female antenna I female propodeum J female T 1 and T 2 K ovipositor sheaths." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81886.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677656" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">3</figureCitation>
) Body dark brown to black and eyes grey in colour. Palpi yellow brown to pale yellow. Antenna dark brown except basal tip of scape and apical portion of pedicel yellowish brown. Ocelli off white. Clypeus dark brown. Mandibles yellowish brown, darker at apical tips. Legs in general dark brown except basal and apical tip of femora, tibiae and basitarsi.
</paragraph>
<caption id="CD44144E2A7B7032A5C533F23514E83A" doi="10.3897/jhr.90.81886.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677656" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" start="Figure 3" startId="F3">
