<subSubSection id="CC04D88B2960150534656BCD110D7FED" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="0FC42A56656B25358C71FD995025B9B5" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="33F4309C73C9031C47FD9E93B53BBC4A" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">
India (Himachal Pradesh). Besides the type locality (Khajjiar), 
<bibRefCitation id="F02647CBE417E34A8E64C4AFC47C6B5B" author="Ahmed, I" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" refId="B1" refString="Ahmed, I, 2017. Taxonomic Studies on Braconidae (Hymenoptera: Insecta) from Jammu Division of the State Jammu and Kashmir, India. Doctoral dissertation, Aligarh Muslim University." title="Taxonomic Studies on Braconidae (Hymenoptera: Insecta) from Jammu Division of the State Jammu and Kashmir, India. Doctoral dissertation, Aligarh Muslim University." year="2017">Ahmed (2017)</bibRefCitation>
also reported the species from the localities of Samba and Poonch (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="37C99A59831ACA6073BBD27E9137C9A0" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Collection localities of Pambolus (Phaenodus) infuscatus Gupta &amp; van Achterberg sp. nov. (in red colour) and Paroplitis khajjiarensis Gupta &amp; Fernandez-Triana sp. nov. (in blue colour)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81886.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677658" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">5A, B</figureCitation>
), in the Jammu and Kashmir state. The type locality (Khajjiar) is approximately 160 kms away from Samba (J&amp;K). Both these states share borders and have a lot of similarity in climate and vegetation.
</paragraph>
<caption id="27A0CBB2059DE535F13CC8C9F995B581" doi="10.3897/jhr.90.81886.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677658" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" start="Figure 5" startId="F5">
<paragraph id="519760C0104B4F846C2FFCED3DB9C007" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis id="6692AE69346B7C4F68B088702F6CEEE4" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Figure 5.</emphasis>
Collection localities of 
<taxonomicName id="674C2E0398D7365DC56A2558D5A363A3" authorityName="Gupta &amp; van Achterberg" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Pambolus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pambolus (Phaenodus) infuscatus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="infuscatus" subGenus="Phaenodus">Pambolus (Phaenodus) infuscatus</taxonomicName>
Gupta &amp; van Achterberg sp. nov. (in red colour) and 
<taxonomicName id="40666986C4C412EE484F773D1C57EE56" authorityName="Gupta &amp; Fernandez-Triana" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Paroplitis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Paroplitis khajjiarensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="khajjiarensis">
<emphasis id="06DCA0935EBA3CADEB7E6A35F3464F11" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Paroplitis khajjiarensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Gupta &amp; 
<normalizedToken id="FF5BB7963CDF7C8FA203C5DAD1ABB9AF" originalValue="Fernández-Triana">Fernandez-Triana</normalizedToken>
sp. nov. (in blue colour).
