</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="02B3B890B6441CC4146B591EDC40EACC" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="FD964BE93C0CF608B36EE7D6EA0D5026" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A1E7AAACB3CB4871BECF076FFEA6EA36" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">
<taxonomicName id="5C27A843D3D376309159A9335B86A377" authorityName="Gupta &amp; Fernandez-Triana" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Paroplitis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Paroplitis khajjiarensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="khajjiarensis">
<emphasis id="4792DFAD24800B0AE1F8A845F05D803D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Paroplitis khajjiarensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was keyed out (as an undescribed species) in 
<bibRefCitation id="7B7478A10E694ECF7816FC365AD868E0" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/dez.68.59641" author="Fujie, S" journalOrPublisher="Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" pagination="33 - 43" refId="B9" refString="Fujie, S, Japoshvili, G, Fernandez-Triana, J, 2021. Review of the world species of Paroplitis Mason, 1981 (Hymenoptera, Braconidae, Microgastrinae), with description of three new species. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift 68 (1): 33 - 43, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/dez.68.59641" title="Review of the world species of Paroplitis Mason, 1981 (Hymenoptera, Braconidae, Microgastrinae), with description of three new species." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/dez.68.59641" volume="68" year="2021">Fujie et al. (2021)</bibRefCitation>
. Those authors were only able to see some images of that species in 
<bibRefCitation id="7FE1AD038D2181F31D791A9589782870" author="Ahmed, I" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" refId="B1" refString="Ahmed, I, 2017. Taxonomic Studies on Braconidae (Hymenoptera: Insecta) from Jammu Division of the State Jammu and Kashmir, India. Doctoral dissertation, Aligarh Muslim University." title="Taxonomic Studies on Braconidae (Hymenoptera: Insecta) from Jammu Division of the State Jammu and Kashmir, India. Doctoral dissertation, Aligarh Muslim University." year="2017">Ahmed (2017</bibRefCitation>
, Plate 32). Our specimens and the one illustrated in 
<bibRefCitation id="86ABA4358D9D6C2D6661BA168C4FC44D" author="Ahmed, I" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" refId="B1" refString="Ahmed, I, 2017. Taxonomic Studies on Braconidae (Hymenoptera: Insecta) from Jammu Division of the State Jammu and Kashmir, India. Doctoral dissertation, Aligarh Muslim University." title="Taxonomic Studies on Braconidae (Hymenoptera: Insecta) from Jammu Division of the State Jammu and Kashmir, India. Doctoral dissertation, Aligarh Muslim University." year="2017">Ahmed (2017)</bibRefCitation>
are very similar and we consider them to represent the same species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="28051EB347CEDEDFCD0C2F68200E9F70" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">
Here we propose a correction to the first couplet of the key by 
<bibRefCitation id="2A95F34665BB146C1E62E2E979D7A725" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/dez.68.59641" author="Fujie, S" journalOrPublisher="Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" pagination="33 - 43" refId="B9" refString="Fujie, S, Japoshvili, G, Fernandez-Triana, J, 2021. Review of the world species of Paroplitis Mason, 1981 (Hymenoptera, Braconidae, Microgastrinae), with description of three new species. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift 68 (1): 33 - 43, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/dez.68.59641" title="Review of the world species of Paroplitis Mason, 1981 (Hymenoptera, Braconidae, Microgastrinae), with description of three new species." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/dez.68.59641" volume="68" year="2021">Fujie et al. (2021)</bibRefCitation>
based on the specimens we have examined, as we found that T2 is not entirely sculptured (as considered by those authors) but there is a smooth area on most of the apical half of the tergite. Thus, the first half of that couplet should be amended to &quot;T1 entirely sculptured and T2 mostly sculptured (with longitudinal striae on lateral sides and basal half of tergite)&quot;. The rest of the key remains the same as in 
<bibRefCitation id="9D0A1B8110CF00E33656BD53398FA5C9" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/dez.68.59641" author="Fujie, S" journalOrPublisher="Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" pagination="33 - 43" refId="B9" refString="Fujie, S, Japoshvili, G, Fernandez-Triana, J, 2021. Review of the world species of Paroplitis Mason, 1981 (Hymenoptera, Braconidae, Microgastrinae), with description of three new species. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift 68 (1): 33 - 43, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/dez.68.59641" title="Review of the world species of Paroplitis Mason, 1981 (Hymenoptera, Braconidae, Microgastrinae), with description of three new species." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/dez.68.59641" volume="68" year="2021">Fujie et al. (2021)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
